listing_desc.151: Located between the New Concord Elementary School and the Library
listing_desc.153: Award-winning Shaker Square Market will be on East and West Bound Shaker Blvd. You will find farms and food producers with fresh produce, meats, dairy, baked goods and more.
listing_desc.154: Located in the beautiful village of Chagrin Falls, this market is filled with Northeast Ohio’s finest farmers. Chagrin Falls Market is located on at Bandstand Triangle Park. You will find farms and food producers with fresh produce, meats, dairy, baked goods and more.
listing_desc.172: Located on Franklin St. in front of the library
listing_desc.217: The Cleveland Clinic Main Campus Market has become a vibrant community gathering place filled with local farmers and artisan food producers. Health screenings and live music make this an educational and fun destination. Located at Crile Mall (across the street from the Crile Building at 2049 E. 100th Street between Carnegie Avenue and Euclid Avenue). You will find farms and food producers with fresh produce, meats, dairy, baked goods and more.
listing_desc.218: Introducing our market at University Hospitals Cleveland Medical Center at Lakeside! Locally sourced lunch is served while you shop at this world-class medical and educational facility, Free parking 30 steps from farm-fresh produce!
listing_desc.219: Seasonal Farmers Market located in the parking lot on West Hopocan Avenue, across from McDonald’s.
listing_desc.220: Support your local farms year-round at Crocker Park’s Winter Farmers Market! Items to look forward to include antibiotic and hormone-free beef, pork, poultry and dairy products, organic maple syrup, honey, farm-fresh eggs, cheeses, winter greens, herbs, apples, potatoes, lettuces, organic grains, specialty goods, and root vegetables. Free parking is available and within close proximity to the market.  We look forward to seeing you soon!
listing_desc.221: Join us in The Van Aken District in the Van Aken Market Hall at the Indoor Winter Farmers Market and enjoy the magnificence of Ohio produce and products. Items to look forward to, including antibiotic and hormone free beef, pork, poultry and dairy products, organic maple syrup, honey, farm-fresh eggs, cheeses, winter greens, herb, apples, potatoes, lettuces, organic grains, specialty goods and root vegetables. Over 20 farms, bakers and artists will participate at the market.
listing_desc.222: Crocker Park Market is conveniently located at Crocker Park in Westlake on the corner of Crocker Road and Detroit Road in front of Fidelity Investments. Find farms and food producers with fresh produce, meats, dairy, baked goods and more.
listing_desc.223: Van Aken District Market is located on Tuttle Road. Find farms and food producers with fresh produce, meats, dairy, baked goods and more.
listing_desc.224: Legacy Village Market is located on Cedar Road in the Capital Grille parking lot. You will find farms and food producers with fresh produce, meats, dairy, baked goods and more.
listing_desc.231: A year round, indoor marketplace in downtown Lancaster

listing_desc.288: Bauman Orchards, started in 1929, currently has a total of 260 acres with 70,000 apple trees and 12,000 peach trees. Now in our fourth generation, we also raise pears, plums, sweet corn, strawberries and blueberries. Our retail farm market in Rittman, Ohio is open year round. We offer seasonal fruit, homemade pies, cookies, and gift baskets. We have two other seasonal farm market locations: Scenic Ridge Fruit Farm in Jeromesville and our Corner Market, also in Rittman.
listing_desc.289: Scenic Ridge Fruit Farm is an extension of Bauman Orchards, offering homegrown peaches July – September, and fresh pressed cider in September and October. Seasonally available products include apples, farm fresh eggs, apple butter, jams, nuts and candies, local honey, maple syrup, sweet corn, melons, tomatoes, green beans, plums, raspberries, pumpkins, squash, gourds.
listing_desc.290: The Corner Market is a seasonal market through Bauman Orchards, located at the Corner of State Routes 585 and 57. The market is open mid-June through October. The market offers many seasonal fruits and vegetables.
listing_desc.291: Family owned and operated orchard since 1878. Our season begins in late July with peaches, nectarines and corn. The selection changes with the seasons. Fall brings apples, pumpkins, gourds and cider. There is also an on-site gift shop and bakery.

listing_desc.297: Family-owned and operated orchard that specializes in growing and selling a wide variety of fresh fruits and cider. We have an extensive selection of apples, peaches, and other seasonal fruits, all harvested at their peak of ripeness. Visitors can enjoy the scenic orchard setting while picking their own fruits on select weekends in October or purchase produce directly from our store August through November.
listing_desc.298: Grower of apples, peaches, cherries and asian pears. The farm shop has fresh fruits available. Pick-your-own is not available.
listing_desc.299: Heartland Orchard is open from late July through mid-December. They grow, pick and sell peaches, apples, and pears. They also offer Christmas tree cutting.

listing_desc.302: Hillcrest Orchard of Walnut Creek is family-owned and operated by the Merle Hershberger family. There are 75 acres of orchard on which 22 varieties of apples and 12 varieties of peach are grown. Our apples and freshly pressed cider are sold at our store, which is open seasonally from August through March.  We also carry local meats and cheeses, a full line of fresh produce, nuts, candies, and snacks.
listing_desc.303: We are a family-owned 105 year-old orchard on the west side of Cincinnati. Our on-farm market sells everything we grow when in season; peaches, plums, pears, apples, and an array of vegetables. We make our own pickles and unpasteurized cider.
listing_desc.304: Orchard with apples, unpasterized cider, veggies, pumpkins, squash and gourds available seasonally. Must call ahead for availability.
listing_desc.305: Farm with fruit and produce available seasonally. Must call ahead for availability.
listing_desc.306: Orchard with apples available seasonally. Must call ahead for availability.
listing_desc.307: Malone Orchards is a family owned and operated farm located in Berlin Heights, Ohio.  We grow a variety of apples including HoneyCrisp and EverCrisp, as well as pears, plums, cherries, pumpkins, gourds, and squash.  We also grow field crops of soybeans and corn.  We operate a seasonal market in Berlin Heights, it is open from September until December (depending on the crop year).
listing_desc.308: The Manfull Family has been growing fresh fruits and vegetables in the small community of Augusta in Carroll County, Ohio for seven generations. The market offers mouthwatering produce during the summer and fall growing seasons, and it opens each spring with delectable baked goods and a variety of jams and fruit butters, local honey, maple syrup, and more.
listing_desc.309: Orchard with fruit available seasonally. Call ahead for hours and availability.
listing_desc.310: Miller Orchards is a family-owned fruit farm, in business for more than 4 generations. At Miller Orchards, we value the integrity that has been passed down through the generations and we provide quality produce at an honest price in a family atmosphere. From simple beginnings in the 1800’s, to the first Miller Orchards retail operation in the early 1960s, the family tradition is carried on today by David and Roger Miller and their families.

listing_desc.326: On our 70 acre farm we grow many deciduous fruit tree varieties including sour cherries, peaches, plums, nectarines, pears, & apples. Stop by the farm with your families for pick your own strawberries and sour cherries. Call or check online for availability.
listing_desc.327: Orchard with local apples available seasonally. Must call ahead for availability.
listing_desc.328: Witts Orchards is a small, family-owned operation growing apples, pears, plums, peaches, nectarines, apricots, and more. The Mini Market location is our packing house.
listing_desc.329: Witts Orchards is a small, family-owned operation growing apples, pears, plums, peaches, nectarines, apricots, and more. The Farm Market location is open seasonally.
listing_desc.330: A 100 acre orchard with one of the largest varieties of apples and peaches in Ohio! Only about 20 minutes from Zanesville, Dresden and New Concord.
listing_desc.331: Burnham Orchards, is a family owned and operated farm, providing great tasting fruits along with a fun experience that includes activities for people of all ages. From pick your own pumpkins to orchard hayrides, we provide a taste of the farm that you just can't get any where else!
listing_desc.332: Orchard with local fruit available seasonally. Must call ahead for availability.
listing_desc.333: Here at Cold Springs, we take great pride in our history and believe in the importance of family and community. We believe in taking care of the land we have been blessed with and in turn it yields delicious and beautiful fruit. Stop by and try a fresh apple—eating locally grown is always in season.
listing_desc.334: Family owned orchard and farm market offering a variety of fruits and locally sourced produce.
listing_desc.335: Our passion is growing fruit. Apples are our primary crop, but that’s not all we grow on our 400-acre farm. Anything that grows on a tree is fair game for us, including peaches, cherries, plums, pears, apricots, nectarines, and grapes; the latter which supply our winemaker next door at Quarry Hill Winery. Please check our Harvest Calendar for specific ripening dates. We also have a nice selection of fresh cider, local produce, and artisan goods as part of our other offerings.
listing_desc.336: Country Maid Orchard includes over 2,000 apple, peach, pear, and plum trees, along with some vegetables, blueberry bushes, and raspberry bushes. All of the ice cream, sherbet, and yogurt that you enjoy at Country Maid Ice Cream is made right here at our only location, where premium ice cream has been made since 1948.
listing_desc.337: Apple Country Farm Market (ACFM) is a family owned and operated business. As an authorized dealer for Weaver Barns and LuxCraft Poly Furniture, we offer quality sheds, buildings, and outdoor furniture year round! Our Farm Market is open seasonally based on our apple harvest (usually early September - the end of October). In addition to the large variety of apples, we also produce fresh cider and seasonal honey varieties. The Country Store in the market carries additional local pantry staples.
listing_desc.338: Apple Hill Or.chards has two locations. The Mansfield location is a hub of retail sales and family-friendly activities. Here, you’ll find our cider press, fruit-themed bakery, observation beehive, rich variety of apples and vegetables, boutique gifts, and unique decorative items.
listing_desc.339: Small family orchard with apples available seasonally, for local pick up. Must call ahead for availability.
listing_desc.340: Sage's Apples is a family farm, part of Ransom Sage Farm, selling apples, pears, seeded grapes, winter squash, garlic, and other local products.
listing_desc.341: Orchard with local fruit available seasonally. Must call ahead for availability.
listing_desc.342: Small local farm offering apples, fresh baked goods, local produce, jams and jellies, maple syrup and local honey.
listing_desc.343: Family farm offering premium quality grain fed beef.
listing_desc.344: Orchard with local fruit available seasonally. Must call ahead for availability.
listing_desc.345: This forty eight-acre farm has lots of animals, as well as several historic museum houses and a Yankee barn, loaded with antiques and historic items. The Stearns House, built in the 1850s and the Gibbs House, built in 1920, are furnished with original antiques. Our farmers market stand will feature our own produce from our gardens, local honey and fresh chicken and duck eggs.
listing_desc.449: A family owned farmers market featuring local produce including bi-color sweet corn, tomatoes, peaches, and more.
listing_desc.471: We raise and sell Rex rabbits, Bielefelder chickens, honeybees, and the different products from each. We also like to teach others about what we have learned and the experiences of each thing we do on the farm.
